<TITLE> Verdict on postman's embezzlement case Feb 6 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 31 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court is set to deliver the verdict on Feb 6 on the case against Secretariat post office official Md Shamsul Karim Talukder on charges of embezzling about Tk 2.25 lakh. Judge Shamsunnahar Begum of the Special Judge's Court-4, set up on the Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban premises, fixed the date after hearing arguments of the state and the defence. Anticorruption Commission assistant director Sheikh Abdus Salam filed the case with Ramna Police Station on April 17 last year. The case accuses Talukder of misappropriating Tk 1. 37 lakh from 37 tax tokens of vehicles from Oct 21, 2003 to Oct 12, 2004 instead of depositing it to the government exchequer. At the same time, he is also accused of embezzling Tk 90,545 through 20 false tax tokens. The charge in the case was framed on Nov 14. Deposition started on Nov 18 and eight persons testified for the state in the case. bdnews24
